
What is a Server ?
->A server is simply a computer or program that gives data or services to other computers over a network.

Think of it like this:
Simple Real-Life Example
Imagine a restaurant.
Customer (You) → asks for food
Waiter/Kitchen → prepares and gives food
In the internet world:
Client = the user’s device (browser, mobile app)
Server = the machine that stores data and sends it when requested

when we install any package of the node it will store in node modules.

package.json maintain that the code is dependent to which packages.

we are creating server using express module 
you can see the example in the express file 

Methods use in express js
1. get -> server se data fetch karwana ho tab use karte h
2. post -> server pe data send karna hoto
3. patch -> server pe data already h aur use update karna hoto
4. delete -> server pe data h aur use delete karna h 